   Infrastucture: The Commission on Building for the 21st Century
    _____________________________________________________________________

   21st Century

   Governor Gray Davis
   Lieutenant Governor Cruz M. Bustamante, Co-Chair
   Maria Contreras-Sweet, Secretary of Business, Transportation and
   Housing, Co-Chair


   The Commission on Building for the 21^st Century was created by
   Governor Gray Davis through Executive Order D-4-99  where it was
   directed to "study the building and infrastructure needs of California,
   with the intent of identifying existing critical infrastructure needs
   and developing a comprehensive long-term capital investment plan for
   financing public building needs, including responsible financial
   approaches and efficiency improvements."

